@interactive_shim_does_not_call_hexa_real /Users/ghost/.hx/bin/hexa shim — the only `.real` reference is line 172 (a *comment* about build/hexa.real). Actual REAL_HEXA assignment is line 60: `REAL_HEXA="${HEXA_RESOLVER_REAL_BIN:-$HOME/.hx/packages/hexa/hexa}"`. So no interactive `hexa run …` on Mac ever exec's `~/.hx/bin/hexa_real`.

@nexus_scripts_no_route /Users/ghost/core/nexus/scripts/bin/hexa_remote — only mentions `~/.hx/bin/hexa_real` for *remote* (linux) hosts (HEXA_REMOTE_BIN default), never for local Mac exec.

@one_legitimate_call_site /Users/ghost/core/hive/state/blockers/design_strategy_cluster_lint_drift.hexa:11 → `fire-cmd /Users/ghost/.hx/bin/hexa_real tool/design_strategy_lint.hexa /Users/ghost/core/hive/.raw --severity warn` (fire-host=local, line 13). This is the ONE active Mac-side call path that exec's ~/.hx/bin/hexa_real.

@switch_history /Users/ghost/core/hive commit 67669b57e (2026-04-25) "feat(design-strategy): hexa_real bypass + Phase F flip helper" — diff in state/blockers/design_strategy_cluster_lint_drift.hexa replaced `HEXA_RESOLVER_NO_REROUTE=1 ... /Users/ghost/.hx/bin/hexa tool/design_strategy_lint.hexa ...` with `/Users/ghost/.hx/bin/hexa_real tool/design_strategy_lint.hexa ...`.

@switch_root_cause empty_run_log: launchd-spawned blocker_autofire detached fire → docker shim hexa-resolver routed through `docker exec hexa-exec` → docker daemon stdout pipeline conflicted with detached parent process group under launchd. Result: 4 cron fires produced 0-byte run_logs despite interactive nohup tests showing 1477-byte verdict=ok output. Bypassing the docker shim (exec the bare arm64 Mach-O directly, zero shim layers) restored output reliability.

@scope_of_bypass narrow — `raw 44 docker hard-landing policy preserved for interactive use; cron fires use bare native (zero shim layers) for output reliability` (commit message, lines 17-20).

@no_other_call_sites grep across nexus/scripts/, nexus/cli/, nexus/tool/, hive/tool/, hive/scripts/, hive/bin/, hive/cli/, hexa-lang/, airgenome/, .hx/packages/hexa/ found ONLY: (a) the one blocker config above, (b) doc/comment refs, (c) Linux-host paths (`/home/aiden/.hx/bin/hexa_real`, `/home/summer/...`, `/root/...`), (d) the parity tool that audits these binaries, (e) ensure_hive_exec.hexa bind-mount strings (Linux-only). No code path on Mac other than launchd-cron blocker fires routes to `~/.hx/bin/hexa_real`.

# 결정

@verdict legitimate — Mac-side `~/.hx/bin/hexa_real` is a deliberate carve-out for launchd-spawned blocker_autofire cron fires. NOT a bug, NOT an orphan from old install, NOT a shim regression. The user's mental model "interactive hexa run on Mac uses the package interpreter" remains correct; the launchd-cron fire path is the documented exception.

@root_cause_of_user_perception scattered rationale: (a) hive/.roadmap line 1580 (one-liner P8.fire-cmd-hexa-real done), (b) hive commit 67669b57e (the *why*), (c) the blocker config itself (the *what*). Operator who sees the running process and asks "why" has to stitch three sources.

